title.narrative: Case management and referral mechanisms are in place to respond to the protection needs of children

description.narrative: UNICEF supported MOSAL and SCFAP to improve the quality of the case management system anchored in a system-wide approach that is rights-based and survivor-focused. The new case management system addresses the issues of women, children and their families holistically and provides comprehensive assessments and interventions that include a multidisciplinary approach and coordinated efforts among key players.; As a result, 22,014 children (120 per cent of the target for 2021) received specialized case management services and 150 children were removed from child labour while 188,013 children participated in structured psychosocial support. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:16/01/2022
